Ghana has had one of Sub-Saharan Africa’s fastest-growing economies in the past few years, but a slowdown because of the new coronavirus is expected to cap growth at between 2-2.5% this year, down from 6.5% in 2019. Addison said there were nevertheless signs that things are picking up and that inflation should return to the bank’s medium-term target of around 8% by the second quarter of 2021. “Leading indicators of economic activity point to recovery,” he told a news conference. --Reuters--